==English==
=== Etymology ===
{{L.}} ''evaginare'', to unsheath; ''ex''-,from +''vagina'', sheath
=== Intransitive verb ===
'''to evaginate''' ''(evaginated, evaginating, evaginates)''
#to [[evert]] a body organ inside surface to outside
=== Transitive verb ===
'''to evaginate''' ''(evaginated, evaginating, evaginates)''
#to cause a body organ or part to become inside-out
=== Pronunciation ===
e*vag"i*nate

